{
  "Cybersecurity Event": {
    "Type": "Vulnerability Discovery",
    "Description": "On November 10, 2017, a vulnerability named #AVGater was discovered. This vulnerability affects certain antivirus products, allowing a non-administrator-level account to restore quarantined files. However, Windows Defender Antivirus, System Center Endpoint Protection (SCEP), Microsoft Security Essentials (MSE), and other Microsoft antimalware products are not affected. The vulnerability can be exploited by malicious applications to restore files that have been detected and quarantined by an antivirus product. The exploit involves creating an NTFS junction from the %System% folder to the folder where the quarantined file is located. This NTFS junction triggers the antivirus product to attempt to restore the file into the %System% folder. This is an old attack vector that has been designed against by Microsoft antimalware products due to their built-in protections against user-account permissions vulnerabilities."
  }
}

