{
  "Cybersecurity Event": "Malvertising Incident",
  "Description": "A malvertising incident occurred on the popular news website salon.com, possibly affecting multiple other websites as well. Users who visited the site's homepage received pop-ups saying 'payload tested' and 'Its working!!!'. These pop-ups were persistent and would not stop even after clicking the 'OK' button. The advertisement was delivered by wwbads via Google's DoubleClick and Adtech (AOL's ad serving platform). The term 'payload' is commonly associated with malware in the security industry. It is suspected that the advertiser may have been testing new methods, but doing so in a live production environment is not acceptable. Another possibility is that the advertiser's platform has been hacked, allowing malicious actors to interfere with the system."
}

